sources.title: ZOMBIE (1964) ORIGINAL DIRECTOR'S CUT
sources.description:
PizzaFLIX Exclusive MOVIE CLASS Edition!
Writer/Director: Del Tenney
Stars: William Joyce, Heather Hewitt, Walter Coy

A playboy novelist travels to Voodoo island where he encounters a witch doctor bent on conquering the world with an army of walking dead. Cool Cocktail Hour score by LON E. NORMAN. After a limited release in 1964, "ZOMBIE" sat on a shelf until 1971 when it was re-edited and re-titled "I EAT YOUR SKIN" for a Grindhouse double feature with "I DRINK YOUR BLOOD.
